  "CEILING": "Synthesis (scRNA-gap + WGS-LOH, different patients, same cancer types). Reported numbers are NOT-arm HLA-LOH AVAILABILITY, PATIENT-LEVEL UPPER BOUNDS \u2014 not clonal (TRACERx ~76% of LUAD LOH subclonal => clonal-only several-fold lower; see scripts/24 clonal_sensitivity), and not multiplied by activator availability (see scripts/27 activator tier). NSCLC-pooled not LUAD. 4-digit allotype = conservative floor; the deployed blocker is A*02-clade cross-reactive so the GROUP number is the better central estimate.",
  "INTERPRETATION": "Single-allele A*02 NOT-arm availability is ~3-6%; a small greedy PANEL of the most common lost alleles recovers most of the 14-28% per-cancer LOH-availability ceiling. The deliverable is the panel-size-vs-availability CURVE + priority allele list. Specificity is ACHIEVABLE but FREQUENCY-BOUNDED by HLA-LOH. To become a true target list, cross each cancer's number with activator availability (scripts/27 tier) and the clonal haircut (scripts/24)."
